1. **Google Analytics with Consent**:
   To integrate Google Analytics while respecting user consent, you can use a consent management platform to ensure analytics scripts run only when consent is granted.

   ```html
   <!-- Google Analytics Global Site Tag -->
   <script async src="https://www.googletagmanager.com/gtag/js?id=GA_MEASUREMENT_ID"></script>
   <script>
     // Initialize Google Analytics only if user consents
     function initializeAnalytics() {
         window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
         function gtag(){dataLayer.push(arguments);}
         gtag('js', new Date());
         gtag('config', 'GA_MEASUREMENT_ID');
     }

     // Check for user consent
     if (userHasConsented) {
       initializeAnalytics();
     }
   </script>
   ```

   In this example, you would check for a user consent flag (`userHasConsented`) before initializing Google Analytics.

